title: Marketing Special Events Coordinator
details: About: Bloomingdale’s makes fashion personal and fun, aspirational yet approachable. Our mission is to guide and inspire our customers to make style a source of creative energy in their lives. We will always strive to make Bloomingdale’s like no other store in the world. Everyone plays a critical role to bring our mission to life. Regardless of position, we believe all colleagues have a voice and access to share their thoughts with every level of leadership. Our colleagues are passionate, driven, entrepreneurial and collaborative. We welcome and embrace diversity of background, thought and opinion while having a lot of fun along the way. Job Overview: The Marketing and Special Events Coordinator assists in the execution of in Bloomingdale’s Integrated Marketing campaigns, including virtual and in-store events. Involvement with external partnerships to drive brand awareness and customer acquisition to positively impact market share on a localized level. The Coordinator will partner with store leadership in the cultivation of Top Clients and maximization of Bloomingdale’s programs dedicated to top tiers .Essential FunctionsAssists in the planning and full execution of all aspects of in-store events and animation that support the direction of the Central strategy. Track post-event results and provides feedback to Central partners. Enhances Central strategy by supporting secured sponsorships, co-branding opportunities and/or community initiatives that build productive local relationships with the intent to build customer base and commerce. Partners with the Store Leadership team in creating curated experiences to build loyalty and share among Bloomingdale’s top spending “Top of the List” (TOL) clients. Maximize opportunities to delight top clients through experiences and special events. Monitor frequency of visits, engagement and spend. Collaborates with the Central Media team to develop local media plans, securing publicity and partnering with brand-appropriate social media influencers and bloggers. Pursues localized opportunities in alignment with Trade Area Marketing and Special Events Leader and store leadership to cultivate customers and build sales. Supports local accelerated growth of focus businesses with event intensification that builds store animation and experience. Guides General Manager(s) as to productive involvement in outside organizations and events. Leverages corporate philanthropy giving programs to maximize community impact and fundraising. May be called upon as point person for external communication locally Qualifications And CompetenciesWe encourage candidates with either a bachelor’s degree or equivalent work experience in a related field to apply.Practices open and continuous communication, values keeping others informed, effectively presenting information in a clear, concise mannerExcellent leadership, facilitation, and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work across functional lines and at many levelsAbility to work a flexible schedule based on department and Company needsPhysical RequirementsHybrid work model that includes in-store and remote work requirementsRequires prolonged periods of sitting, with occasional standingEvent execution requires walking, bending, reaching, hearing and talkingContinuous use of computers and other office equipmentFrequently lift/move up to 25 lbs.

title: Learning & Wellness Director
details: Job Title: Learning & Wellness DirectorDepartment: People DepartmentLocation: Remote. This position requires an ability to travel.Reports To: Chief People OfficerSupervises: Potential for 2 direct reportsContext: At the Sierra Club, we believe in the power of interdependence. Together, we remain committed to the fight for a healthy climate built on a foundation of environmental, racial, economic, and gender justice – a future where all people benefit from a healthy, thriving planet and a direct connection to nature. As the climate crisis and deeply entrenched systemic racism all fuel injustice, we will continue to fight for a bold, transformational agenda that recognizes the interconnectedness between our planet, our humanity, and our future. By recognizing that our destinies are tied, we continue to name that all things are fundamentally connected, and the overlap between ecology, race, gender, and representative government will move to either advance our collective humanity or to oppress it. Sierra Club has close to 800 staff across the country and a network of 64 local chapters that are led and fueled by thousands of volunteers. We are also proud to be a unionized employer, with three labor unions representing more than half of our employees.Scope: The Learning & Wellness Director will be responsible for designing and overseeing the strategic implementation of a comprehensive community-wide experiential learning and development program for the organization utilizing Decolonize Design’s Belonging, Dignity, Justice and Joy Framework (BDJJ). This learning program will help our community members develop and build the analysis, skills and practices needed to live our core organizational values every day and contribute to a highly effective and balanced organization at each stage of the employee and volunteer lifecycle. The Learning & Wellness Director will build and manage a small team that develops and delivers varied learning strategies and activities, and will coordinate and collaborate with key staff and partners throughout the organization to leverage and align with existing learning and training efforts.This role works to ensure we embed our values in all we do as individuals and as an organization.Job Activities Include But Are Not Limited To Develop Org-Wide Learning & Development Strategy. This strategy will provide skill building and learning for staff and volunteers throughout the lifecycle of their engagement with Sierra Club, and will be focused on foundational competencies needed to live our values and thrive within the organization. It will be designed to meet the needs of staff and volunteers at all levels from onboarding, to annual performance reviews and leadership development. It will complement, rather than duplicate, other learning and training efforts throughout the organization and fill critical training gaps. It will strategically incorporate a mix of virtual and live learning engagements, and optimize Sierra Club’s online learning management system. The innovative strategy will utilize varied training tools, techniques, and resources to meet the needs of our community.  Lead Immersive Learning EcoSystem Development. Working in partnership with key staff and volunteers, lead and oversee implementation of the learning and development strategy and program grounded in Belonging, Dignity, Justice & Joy principles with a focus on employee and volunteer lifecycle training and growth opportunities. Work to develop, synthesize, and socialize core competencies and curriculum to be used across audiences. Programming will include, but is not limited to, foundational training as well as legally required training, and will be flexible enough to meet emerging needs.  Measure Effectiveness and Impact. Lead holistic learning program development inclusive of assessment, design, implementation, evaluation and follow-up. Assess the needs of staff and volunteer stakeholders, organizational trends, and priorities, to deliver tailored training. Develop mechanisms to track practice change and learning and traning outcomes in order to measure impact, and ensure organizational and legal compliance. Collect feedback on participant experience to make iterative improvements over time. Provide reports to leadership on programmatic goals and outcomes. Provide direction to staff and volunteer leaders and managers to enhance and further develop learning efforts.  Build and Manage Learning & Development Team. Leverage existing capacity when appropriate and make new hires when possible. As part of staff management, make hiring, salary, promotion and termination decisions; co-develop and oversee work plans; provide ongoing mentorship, coaching and professional development; provide ongoing feedback and conduct annual reviews; and provide support and guidance to ensure joyful approaches are utilized. As needed, lead and manage collaborative cross-capacity teams.  Provide Advice and Guidance on Targeted Learning. Act as an internal subject matter expert on learning and development by providing advice and guidance to stakeholders throughout the organization who are developing targeted learning activities. Provide oversight to align Chapter, Department, and volunteer learning activities with organizational strategy, standards of conduct, policy compliance, and cultural initiatives. Create a process to review and approve external training contracts for alignment with organizational strategy, policy, and core values. The successful candidate must have the following skills and experience: Learning & Development Leadership. You have extensive work experience in Learning and Development and the People relations fields that includes leading a large scale training program. You have advanced skill in training facilitation and curriculum design and are open to supporting the guiding principles of Belonging, Dignity, Justice and Joy. You have experience in developing and delivering employee and volunteer lifecycle learning content including but not limited to: onboarding, performance, leadership and management development, belonging embedment, and legally mandated workplace training. You bring experience developing and implementing impactful and creative adult learning activities, training and workshops, both in-person and online, in an organizational context that results in measurable practice and culture change. You have experience creating resources, tools, and processes to build on learning engagements.  Strategic Senior Leadership. You display strategic vision and strong leadership capabilities. You have experience designing foundational learning programs that develop individuals and contribute to organizational culture. You have partnered with senior leaders to develop a shared analysis of organizational needs and collectively advanced solutions and interventions. You have demonstrated success in planning and implementing new strategies and programs across a large organization or institution.  Project Management. You have a track record of managing large scale projects from end to end. You utilize systems thinking to navigate complexity and adapt to dynamic conditions. You bring strong project management and facilitation skills. You have developed a structured process with support systems that enable staff, volunteers and leaders to prepare for and adapt to change.  Team Management. You bring prior experience in the management of staff, volunteers, consultants, and/or teams. Advanced relational and interpersonal skills include: social-emotional awareness, coaching and skill-building, communication, building relationships across differences, navigating and resolving conflict, giving and receiving feedback.  Committed to evolution. You are committed to continuously deepening and evolving your own understanding of systems of oppression through study, openness, and humility. And you easily recognize your own relationship to privilege and power, examining and shifting your behaviors as appropriate.  Uplifting and additive. You see mistakes as opportunities for growth; problems as catalysts for solutions, and inspire others along the journey. You carry a constructive approach, can-do attitude, a sense of humor, and authentic kindness wherever you go. Compensation And BenefitsThe salary range or salary for this position is $155,00-165,000. This position is remote and requires the ability to travel.The Sierra Club offers a competitive salary package commensurate with skills and experience plus excellent benefits that include medical, dental, and vision coverage, and a retirement savings 401(k) plan.This is a category 3, exempt, non-represented, managerial and/or supervisory, and confidential position.Sierra Club values the expertise and talents of foreign nationals. Sierra Club sponsors both nonimmigrant and immigrant visas when certain criteria are met, based on immigration laws and organizational needs. Such sponsorship is at the discretion of the Department Head and Sierra Club People Department in consultation with the employee’s manager. The Sierra Club cannot guarantee the approval of a visa petition. The Sierra Club is an equal opportunity employer committed to workforce belonging. To Apply Please submit your resume here.The Sierra Club provides equal employment and advancement opportunities to all staff members. Employment decisions are based on merit, qualifications, lived experience and skills. The Sierra Club does not discriminate in employment opportunities or practices on the basis of race, color, creed, religion, national origin, immigration status, socioeconomic status, ancestry, age, size, sex, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, familial status, veteran status, disability, AIDS/HIV status, medical condition, prior conviction, arrest history, traits historically associated with race, including, but not limited to, hair texture and protective hairstyles, or any other characteristic protected by law.The Sierra Club values applicants who are people that identify as Black, Indigenous, and other minoritized groups; women; queer, transgender, gender non-conforming, and gender fluid people.
